      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis index QoI on the finest two mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed with refinement ratio r = 1.3. GCI values for the scalar hemolysis index were 3.8% (medium-to-fine) and 8.1% (coarse-to-medium). The fine mesh (14.2 M cells) was selected for all production runs, yielding GCI < 5% for the primary QoI. Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and matched to simulation inputs within stated measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions were sourced from the FDA critical path initiative dataset. Inlet flow rates (2.5, 3.5, 4.5, 5.0, 6.0 L/min) and rotational speeds (2400, 3500 RPM) were replicated in simulation boundary conditions. Blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) were matched. Measurement uncertainties were within ±2% of nominal values. Level 2 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
